<p>Azure Service queues and Azure Storage queues both exist </p>  <p>They have some characteristics like :</p>  <ol> <li><p>Azure Service queues have a better transactional handling with the PeekLock mode where the message really disappear of the queue on the <code>BrokeredMessage.Complete()</code> call.</p></li> <li><p>Azure Storage queues alllow to use more space : 100 Gb versus 5Gb for Azure Service Bus Queues</p></li> </ol>  <p>Could you quote what are the times to use or not to use a given queue ?<br> And what are the other interesting characteristics or behaviors of queues.</p>  <p>Thanks</p>